         <abstract id="aspace_7243f1ca189b1f14af752fcad8093341">The collection consists of cashbooks, correspondence, daybooks, invoices, journals, ledgers and other materials documenting the financial operations of Elihu Geer's printing shop and stationery business in Hartford, Connecticut. Material relating to his publication of the <title render="italic">
               <part>Hartford Journal</part>
            </title> and the <title render="italic">
               <part>Congregationalist</part>
            </title> is also included in the collection.</abstract>
